    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<h1>RUTH (Person)</h1><p>A Moabitess and the widow of Mahlon, the son of Naomi and Elimelech, who were Ephrathites from Bethlehem. Naomi and Elimelech moved to Moab due to a famine in Judah. After Elimelech and Naomi&apos;s two sons died, Naomi returned to Bethlehem with her daughter-in-law Ruth during the barley harvest  (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:4-Ruth1:22\">Ruth 1:4</a><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:4-Ruth1:22\">–</a><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:4-Ruth1:22\">22</a>). While gleaning in the barley fields of Boaz, Ruth found favor in his eyes (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:2-Ruth2:22\">Ruth 2:2</a><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:2-Ruth2:22\">–</a><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:2-Ruth2:22\">22</a>). She later married Boaz. He, as the nearest family member, purchased Naomi&apos;s estate to keep it in the family. (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:5-Ruth4:13\">Ruth 4:5</a><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:5-Ruth4:13\">–</a><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:5-Ruth4:13\">13</a>). Ruth is mentioned in Matthew’s family list of Christ as the mother of Obed and the great-grandmother of David (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:5\">Matthew 1:5</a>).</p><p><em>See also</em> <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"4580\" data-resourceType=\"TyndaleBibleDictionary\">Genealogy of Jesus Christ</span>; <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"7243\" data-resourceType=\"TyndaleBibleDictionary\">Ruth, Book of</span>.</p>",
